<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E27FFA5FF7B8AC8FD0DFE51" blockId="6.[166,641,431,458]" box="[166,641,431,458]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
<heading id="D09F552D2E27FFA5FF7B8AC8FD0DFE51" box="[166,641,431,458]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FF7B8AC8FD0DFE51" authority="Lincicome, 1943" authorityName="Lincicome" authorityYear="1943" box="[166,641,431,458]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Corynosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="obtuscens">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FF7B8AC8FE35FE51" bold="true" box="[166,441,431,458]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Corynosoma obtuscens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FE1D8AC8FD0DFE51" author="Lincicome, D. R." box="[448,641,431,458]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="102 - 106" refId="ref7371" refString="Lincicome, D. R. 1943. Acanthocephala of the genus Corynosoma from the California sea lion. Journal of Parasitology, 29, 102 - 106." type="journal article" year="1943">Lincicome, 1943</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E27FFA5FF068A88FD1FFD91" blockId="6.[166,1225,495,1290]" box="[219,659,495,522]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
D e s c r i p t i o n (
<figureCitation id="1353FEC42E27FFA5FE4F8A88FE5DFD91" box="[402,465,495,522]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1735,1757]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,186,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-14@5.[220,1178,174,1703]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Acanthocephalan species from California sea lions (Zalophus californianus): A — Corynosoma strumosum, total view of adult male; B — Corynosoma obtuscens, total view of female; C — Profilicollis altmani, total view of immature male; D — Andracantha phalacrocoracis, anterior part of female; E — Andrcantha sp., total view of immature female. Scale bars: A, B, C, E — 1 mm, D — 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454657/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">figs 1</figureCitation>
, B; 
<figureCitation id="1353FEC42E27FFA5FE208A88FD81FD91" box="[509,525,495,522]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,207,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[235,1128,177,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-14@7.[230,1175,142,1621]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. Acanthocephalan species from California sea lions (Zalophus californianus): A — Andracantha sp., total view of immature male. Scale bar 1 mm; B — Andracantha sp., proboscis of female. Scale bar 500 μm; C — Andracantha sp., total view of immature female. Scale bar 1 mm; D — Andracantha phalacrocoracis, spines of ventral surface. Scale bar 1 mm; E — Corynosoma obtuscens, transitional hooks. Scale bar 50 μm; F — Corynosoma strumosum, transitional hooks. Scale bar 50 μm; G — Profilicollis altmani, longitudinal row of hooks. Scale bar 100 μm; H — Andracantha sp., posterior part of female. Scale bar 500 μm; J — Andracantha sp., longitudinal row of hooks.Scale bar 100 μm; K — Andracantha phalacrocoracis, longitudinal row of hooks. Scale bar 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454661/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">2</figureCitation>
, F; 
<tableCitation id="C6EAD7FA2E27FFA5FDE88A88FD0AFD91" box="[565,646,495,522]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="3.[165,232,505,527]" captionText="Table 2. Morphological features of Acanthocephala specimens found in California sea lions (Zalophus californianus). All measurements are in micrometers unless otherwise stated" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C372B1CA2E27FFA5FF068968FD5DFA91" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E27FFA5FF068968FDFBFCF1" blockId="6.[166,1225,495,1290]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
General. Small acanthocephalans. Trunk with dilatation in its anterior part. Spine field extends to 609–976 dorsally, and to posterior end of trunk ventrally, in males with bare zone between ventral and genital spines. Length of somatic spines increasing from anterior (17–37) to posterior (36–44). Genital spines present, 41–49 long. Proboscis almost cylindrical, with widening in its posterior quarter. Proboscis with 17–19 longitudinal rows of 11–14 hooks each. First 9–11 hooks large, with simple roots directed posteriorly. Next 1–2 hooks transitional with small roots in shape of inverted Y (
<figureCitation id="1353FEC42E27FFA5FC4489A8FC5BFD71" box="[921,983,719,746]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,207,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[235,1128,177,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-14@7.[230,1175,142,1621]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. Acanthocephalan species from California sea lions (Zalophus californianus): A — Andracantha sp., total view of immature male. Scale bar 1 mm; B — Andracantha sp., proboscis of female. Scale bar 500 μm; C — Andracantha sp., total view of immature female. Scale bar 1 mm; D — Andracantha phalacrocoracis, spines of ventral surface. Scale bar 1 mm; E — Corynosoma obtuscens, transitional hooks. Scale bar 50 μm; F — Corynosoma strumosum, transitional hooks. Scale bar 50 μm; G — Profilicollis altmani, longitudinal row of hooks. Scale bar 100 μm; H — Andracantha sp., posterior part of female. Scale bar 500 μm; J — Andracantha sp., longitudinal row of hooks.Scale bar 100 μm; K — Andracantha phalacrocoracis, longitudinal row of hooks. Scale bar 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454661/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, F). Next 2–3 hooks spiniform, with simple roots directed anteriorly or without roots. Largest hooks 9 
<superScript id="7C1D4F092E27FFA5FB598989FB1EFD67" attach="left" box="[1156,1170,750,764]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">th</superScript>
and 10 
<superScript id="7C1D4F092E27FFA5FF1F8869FF5CFC87" attach="none" box="[194,208,782,796]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">th</superScript>
. Proboscis receptacle double-walled. Neck 145–261 long. Lemnisci 505–901 long, attached in neck and extending to level of proboscis receptacle bottom or slightly posterior to it. Gonopore subterminal in both sexes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E27FFA5FF068808FD5DFA91" blockId="6.[166,1225,495,1290]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
R e m a r k s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FEB88817FDE0FC12" authorityName="Lincicome" authorityYear="1943" box="[357,620,879,906]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Corynosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="obtuscens">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FEB88817FDE0FC12" box="[357,620,879,906]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Corynosoma obtuscens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common parasite of sea lions (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FC228808FB49FC11" author="Lincicome, D. R." box="[1023,1221,879,906]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="102 - 106" refId="ref7371" refString="Lincicome, D. R. 1943. Acanthocephala of the genus Corynosoma from the California sea lion. Journal of Parasitology, 29, 102 - 106." type="journal article" year="1943">Lincicome, 1943</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FF7B88E8FE0FFC31" author="Van Cleave, H. J." box="[166,387,911,938]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref8731" refString="Van Cleave, H. J. 1953 a. A preliminary analysis of the acanthocephalan genus Corynosoma in Mammals of North America. Journal of Parasitology, 39, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1953">Van Cleave, 1953 a</bibRefCitation>
, b). The species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FCDC88E8FC42FC31" author="Lincicome, D. R." box="[769,974,911,938]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="102 - 106" refId="ref7371" refString="Lincicome, D. R. 1943. Acanthocephala of the genus Corynosoma from the California sea lion. Journal of Parasitology, 29, 102 - 106." type="journal article" year="1943">Lincicome (1943)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FBCE88F7FB44FC32" authorityName="Lesson" authorityYear="1828" box="[1043,1224,911,938]" class="Mammalia" family="Otariidae" genus="Zalophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="californianus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FBCE88F7FBA8FC32" box="[1043,1060,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Z</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FBED88E8FB44FC32" box="[1072,1224,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">californianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the San Diego Zoo, 
<collectingRegion id="49AC2CA32E27FFA5FE3588C8FDEDFC51" box="[488,609,943,970]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37FA2D12E27FFA5FDAC88C8FD20FC51" box="[625,684,943,970]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">USA</collectingCountry>
. It was also registered in northern fur seals (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FF6D88A8FD85FC71" authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" box="[176,521,975,1002]" class="Mammalia" family="Otariidae" genus="Callorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ursinus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FF6D88A8FE18FC72" box="[176,404,975,1001]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Callorhinus ursinus</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
) and South American sea lions (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FC5E88B7FB0CFC71" authority="Peron" authorityName="Peron" box="[899,1152,975,1002]" class="Mammalia" family="Otariidae" genus="Otaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="byronia">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FC5E88B7FBBDFC72" box="[899,1073,975,1002]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Otaria byronia</emphasis>
Péron
</taxonomicName>
) from the 
<collectingRegion id="49AC2CA32E27FFA5FF098888FEC7FB91" box="[212,331,1007,1034]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">California</collectingRegion>
coast, in the Gulf of Mexico, off the coast of South America and in 
<collectingRegion id="49AC2CA32E27FFA5FBA78888FB45FB91" box="[1146,1225,1007,1034]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Alaska</collectingRegion>
(Van Cleve, 1953 a, b), and from domestic dogs in 
<collectingCountry id="F37FA2D12E27FFA5FCC58F68FCC3FBB1" box="[792,847,1039,1066]" name="Peru" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FCBC8F68FBD8FBB1" author="Cabrera, R. &amp; Rojas, R. &amp; Davalos, M." box="[865,1108,1039,1066]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="59 - 62" refId="ref6345" refString="Cabrera, R., Rojas, R., Davalos, M. 1999. Corynosoma obtuscens Lincicome, 1943 (Acanthocephala: Polymorphidae) in Canis familiaris de la Ciudad de Chincha, Peru. Parasitologia al dia, 23, 59 - 62." type="journal article" year="1999">Cabrera et al., 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Juvenile specimens were also registered in sea otter (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FD1C8F48FC68FBD1" authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" box="[705,996,1071,1098]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" genus="Enhydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lutris">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FD1C8F48FCE0FBD2" box="[705,876,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Enhydra lutris</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FC238F48FF6FFBF1" author="Ward, H. L. &amp; Winter, H. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="154 - 156" refId="ref8791" refString="Ward, H. L., Winter, H. A. 1952. Juvenile Acanthocephala from the yellowfin croaker, Umbrina roncador, with description of a new species of the genus Arhythmorhynchus. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, 71, 154 - 156." type="journal article" year="1952">Ward &amp; Winter, 1952</bibRefCitation>
). Domestic dogs were successfully infected experimentally with cystacanths collected from fish (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FEFC8F08FDC0FB11" author="Castro, M. &amp; Martinez, R." box="[289,588,1135,1162]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="26 - 30" refId="ref6463" refString="Castro, M., Martinez, R. 2004. Proceso del desarrollo de Corynosoma obtuscens (Acanthocephala: Polymorphidae) en Canis familiaris y su posible implicancia en slud publica. Parasitologia Latinoamericana, 59, 26 - 30." type="journal article" year="2004">Castro &amp; Martínez, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Our material corresponds to the original description provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FEE38FE8FD9EFB31" author="Lincicome, D. R." box="[318,530,1167,1194]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="102 - 106" refId="ref7371" refString="Lincicome, D. R. 1943. Acanthocephala of the genus Corynosoma from the California sea lion. Journal of Parasitology, 29, 102 - 106." type="journal article" year="1943">Lincicome (1943)</bibRefCitation>
. Intermediate hosts for 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FCF28FF7FC4CFB32" authorityName="Lincicome" authorityYear="1943" box="[815,960,1167,1194]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Corynosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="obtuscens">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FCF28FF7FC4CFB32" box="[815,960,1167,1194]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">C. obtuscens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown. Several species of fishes (paratenic hosts) off the Pacific coast of South America were found to be infected with cystacanths of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E27FFA5FE2B8FB7FD0AFB72" authorityName="Lincicome" authorityYear="1943" box="[502,646,1231,1258]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Corynosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="obtuscens">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E27FFA5FE2B8FB7FD0AFB72" box="[502,646,1231,1258]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">C. obtuscens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with prevalence up to 60 % (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E27FFA5FC028FA8FF6DFA91" author="Tantalean, M. &amp; Huiza, A." pageId="6" pageNumber="187" pagination="53 - 101" refId="ref8622" refString="Tantalean, M., Huiza, A. 1994. Sinopsis de los parasitos de peces marinos de la costa peruana. Biotempo, 1, 53 - 101." type="journal article" year="1994">Tantaleán &amp; Huiza, 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
